6:
So this is the Kaleidoscope. What a
strange place...
10:
Strange barely describes it. It shifts
and turns with time like a living
creature, sometimes wandering into
other worlds.
13:
Mysterious, as most blessings are.
This labyrinth is the source of
Palpebra's wealth, right?
15:
If only the royals would let hunters
wander in and out of the ruins just
as freely, my country might flourish
the same way... But somehow, I don't
see that happening.
21:
Helps that Palpebra's not a country
in the first place.
29:
Haha. Here, my brush is a matter of
convenience, rather than necessity.
30:
And I am just your average traveler.
Everything is so different...
51:
Looks like you're unhurt. Thank
goodness.
56:
You are no adventurer. What brings
you to the Kaleidoscope?
61: If it was on a dare, I—
64:
N-no! Of course not! I need
elemental gems!
65:
The topsoil, back at my village... It's
been sucked dry of nutrients. We
haven't had a good harvest for
years.
69: What's soil got to do with gems?
72:
Huh? I mean, it can be turned into
fertilizer.
78:
Y-yeah... I don't know much about
the process, but I heard if you
provide gems to the Arcane Arts
Academy, they can make some
pretty potent stuff.
80:
That's why I'm not going home until
I've gotten my hands on at least a
shard!
84:
But it's dangerous for you to be here
alone. Why didn't someone else
from the village come with you?
87:
Everyone thinks the gem thing is just
a hocus-pocus scam. But if I could
just prove it actually works...
90:
Very well. We have some gems to
spare—
95: Wait. Light, you know the saying.
98:
Give a man a fish, he'll eat for a day.
But teach a man to fish...
103:
Then you taught him how to trawl
safely for gems.
107:
Yes. The shallows shouldn’t pose a
danger to him anymore.
110:
That man was a trailblazer. He'll be
back to the Kaleidoscope.
115:
And the next time around, we may
not be there to aid him. Shrewd
foresight, Rakisha.
117: I just didn't want his journey to end.
122:
If I'm gonna be completely honest
though, I would've liked him to buy
his gems from the Guild.
126: Who knew gems could be so useful?
129:
I mean, the Arcane Arts Academy is
coming up with nifty inventions all
the time. They gave us streetlights
and water filtration...
132:
But their biggest contribution was to
farming. Crops are the number one
force behind Palpebra's economy.
135:
By the way, we're gonna dispatch
some experts to the guy's village.
Teach 'em the most efficient way of
using the fertilizer and all that good
stuff.
138: The Guild offers that much support?
141:
Apparently, top brass used to hoard
this kind of information. For the
usual reason of "knowledge is
power."
144:
But then they realized if they shared
that power, the city grew stronger
as a whole.
148: This really is a strange place...
153:
You still tryin' to find ways to be a
savior to the desert? Thought you
were starting to enjoy life as an
"average adventurer."
159:
But it seems no matter how far I
travel, my heart will always remain
where it all started.
162: Heh. I guess it's just part of who I am.
170:
...Mind taking me to the Arcane Arts
Academy sometime?
171: I need to learn about those gems.
175: I am also curious. Let's go together.
177:
Thanks, Stella. We can help each
other out.
180: Will you be joining us, Nimbus?
189:
You've never taken no for an answer,
Rakisha.
